 {"id":"frankenredis-hjub","title":"s5su part c: stream decoder for RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS (15) — entries only","description":"Extend fr-persist::decode_rdb to accept upstream type-15 stream records and reconstruct RdbValue::Stream(entries, watermark, []). No consumer groups yet — blank Vec. Uses the listpack decoder from s5su-b.\n\nScope:\n  * Read radix tree pair count, iterate each (stream-id, listpack) pair.\n  * Decode listpack entries into (ms, seq, fields) tuples.\n  * Populate watermark from stream metadata (last_id).\n  * Leave consumer_groups empty (covered by s5su-d).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:17:58.348959392Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T06:52:05.947261Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T06:52:05.947261Z","close_reason":"Landed in e498ffd (s5su part c: stream entry decoder).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"frankenredis-hjzc","title":"[HIGH] SCAN-family: iteration order + invalid-cursor wording + NOVALUES support delta","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_scan_matches_runtime: (a) SCAN/HSCAN/SSCAN/ZSCAN return entries in hashbrown probe order vs upstream's dict-array order (same unspecified-semantics case as HGETALL — can canonicalize in live harness). (b) Invalid/negative cursor emits 'ERR value is not an integer or out of range' vs upstream 'ERR invalid cursor'; negative cursor should be clamped to 0 per upstream (returns empty reply). (c) COUNT 0 rejected with generic parse error vs upstream 'ERR syntax error'. (d) HSCAN/ZSCAN NOVALUES flag is a Redis 7.4 feature — we support it, vendored 7.2.4 rejects with syntax error. Fix: add scan-pair canonicalizer in live_oracle_frames_match + align fr-command cursor-parse error wording. NOVALUES cases XFAIL until vendored redis is upgraded to 7.4.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T07:20:18.972139187Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T08:24:14.929798Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T08:24:14.929798Z","close_reason":"Aligned SCAN-family cursor errors, order canonicalization, and live XFAIL coverage"}
+{"id":"frankenredis-hjzc","title":"[HIGH] SCAN-family: iteration order + invalid-cursor wording + NOVALUES support delta","description":"Surfaced by live_redis_core_scan_matches_runtime: (a) SCAN/HSCAN/SSCAN/ZSCAN return entries in hashbrown probe order vs upstream's dict-array order (same unspecified-semantics case as HGETALL — can canonicalize in live harness). (b) Invalid/negative cursor emits 'ERR value is not an integer or out of range' vs upstream 'ERR invalid cursor'; negative cursor should be clamped to 0 per upstream (returns empty reply). (c) COUNT 0 rejected with generic parse error vs upstream 'ERR syntax error'. (d) HSCAN/ZSCAN NOVALUES flag is a Redis 7.4 feature — we support it, vendored 7.2.4 rejects with syntax error. Fix: add scan-pair canonicalizer in live_oracle_frames_match + align fr-command cursor-parse error wording. NOVALUES cases XFAIL until vendored redis is upgraded to 7.4.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T07:20:18.972139187Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T08:40:15.768174000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"closed_at":"2026-04-24T08:40:15.768174000Z","close_reason":"Fixed in ad52472: SCAN-family cursor/count error wording aligned with upstream, negative cursor handling (ULONG_MAX for DB-level SCAN, clamp-to-0 for HSCAN/SSCAN/ZSCAN listpack semantics), live_oracle_scan_family_order_matches canonicalizer for iteration-order-unstable replies, 7.4 NOVALUES XFAIL. core_scan live 103/103 pass (was 91/113). All 169 fr-conformance lib tests pass."}
